SIMPLE: intrepidity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intrepidity
<hw>In`tre*pid"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intr⟦eacute⟧pidit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state
of being intrepid; fearless bravery; courage; resoluteness;
valor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sir Roger had acquitted himself of two or three sentences with a
look of much business and great <qex>intrepidity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Courage; heroism; bravery; fortitude; gallantry;
valor. See <er>Courage</er>, <er>Heroism</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrepidly</ent>⟦br⟧
